Commentary Text: Pretorius to Hrithik Shokeen, no run, Hrithik Shokeen reviews and loses. Commentary Text: Tushar Deshpande to Tim David, out Caught by Rahane!! Tushar Deshpande has his revenge. It's a big wicket for Tim David was beginning to look dangerous. A slower ball off-cutter outside off, David did not go hard on the pull, was a sort of a half-hearted shot, a flat hit but straight to the fielder at deep mid-wicket. Rahane is as safe as they come, he does not drop that and David is livid as he walks back. Deshpande though is venting out all his frustration as he utters a few curse words. Tim David c Rahane b Tushar Deshpande 31(22) [4s-1 6s-2]

Commentary Text: Magala to Tristan Stubbs, out Caught by Gaikwad!! Good tag-team work from Pretorius and Gaikwad sees the end of Tristan Stubbs. Tristan Stubbs comes down the track and it's another slower ball off-cutter outside off, he slices the loft, Pretorius slightly misjudged that as he tracked back at long-off, takes it over his head but losing his balance and going outside the cushions, so lobs it up and Gaikwad from long-on is there to take a simple catch. No need for the third ump to check if it was a clean catch. Tristan Stubbs c Gaikwad b Magala 5(10)

Commentary Text: Jadeja to Tilak Varma, out Lbw!! Jadeja ends his spell with a big wicket. Slowed it down after the last ball, on off and middle, Tilak Varma gets forward to flick and plays across the line, misses and is rapped on the pads low. No inside-edge and it is crashing into the top of middle-stump. Varma wastes a review even though one can't blame him for taking it considering his side's situation. Tilak Varma lbw b Jadeja 22(18) [4s-2 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Chawla to Rahane, out Caught by Suryakumar Yadav!! And that's what MI wanted Chawla to do and he has done it. The danger man is gone. The batter wanted to punch it down the ground but ended up cue-ending to the man at long-on. Simple take for the fielder in the deep. Did the ball hold on to the deck a little? Might well have been the case as Rahane has seldom mistimed anything barring this. The moment he hit it, he knew it. But an excellent knock comes to an end.
